    "## 3. Define Model Architecture\n",
    "\n",
    "Design a CNN with convolutional blocks, pooling, dropout, and dense layers."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "architecture_description = \"\"\"\n",
    "=== CNN ARCHITECTURE DESIGN ===\n",
    "\n",
    "**Model: Sequential CNN for Binary Image Classification**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Convolutional Blocks:**\n",
    "1. Block 1: Conv2D(32 filters, 3x3) → ReLU → Conv2D(32) → ReLU → MaxPool(2x2)\n",
    "   - Learns low-level features: edges, simple textures\n",
    "   - Output: 90x90x32\n",
    "\n",
    "2. Block 2: Conv2D(64 filters, 3x3) → ReLU → Conv2D(64) → ReLU → MaxPool(2x2)\n",
    "   - Combines low-level features into mid-level patterns\n",
    "   - Output: 45x45x64\n",
    "\n",
    "3. Block 3: Conv2D(128 filters, 3x3) → ReLU → Conv2D(128) → ReLU → MaxPool(2x2)\n",
    "   - Learns higher-level semantic features\n",
    "   - Output: 22x22x128 → 11x11x128\n",
    "\n",
    "**Spatial Reduction via MaxPooling:**\n",
    "- Reduces spatial dimensions (180→90→45→22→11)\n",
    "- Provides translational invariance (small shifts don't affect output)\n",
    "- Reduces parameters and computation\n",
    "\n",
    "**Dropout for Regularization:**\n",
    "- 0.5 dropout after pooling layers\n",
    "- Randomly deactivates neurons during training\n",
    "- Forces network to learn redundant representations\n",
    "- Reduces co-adaptation and overfitting\n",
    "\n",
    "**Dense Classification Head:**\n",
    "- Flatten: 11x11x128 = 15,488 features\n",
    "- Dense(256) → ReLU → Dropout(0.5)\n",
    "- Dense(1) → Sigmoid\n",
    "- Sigmoid output in [0,1] for binary probability: P(Dog)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Loss Function: Binary Crossentropy**\n",
    "- Correct for Bernoulli targets (binary classification)\n",
    "- Penalizes confident wrong predictions\n",
    "\n",
    "**Total Parameters: ~2.2M (reasonable for 180x180 images on CPU/GPU)**\n",
    "\"\"\"\nprint(architecture_description)"
   ]
